{
  "id": 5986946868445184,
  "name": "Stop re-queueing LaunchParams on reload",
  "summary": "Prevent the launchQueue from re-sending the last LaunchParams (including file handles) when a user reloads the page. Currently, a page refresh triggers the launch consumer again with the data from the original launch. This change ensures that a reload is treated as a standard navigation rather than a \"re-launch,\" and the launchQueue will not be populated with duplicate files unless a new file launch event occurs. The re-queueing was never spec'd, and was an unfortunate never-removed stop-gap that was implemented before file handles could be saved to IndexedDB.",
