  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "The current behavior of re-sending file handles on reload is often unexpected and leads to buggy user experiences. For example, an app might prompt a user to \"save changes\" or \"overwrite file\" every time they refresh the page because the app logic thinks a new file was just opened. Developers currently have to write custom logic to detect reloads and ignore these redundant events, and based on developer feedback certain edge cases are impossible to avoid. This change aligns the API with developer expectations that a \"reload\" should refresh the current state rather than re-trigger the initial entry-point logic.\n\nThe re-queueing was never spec'd, and was an unfortunate never-removed stop-gap that was implemented before file handles were writable to IndexedDB.\n\nhttps://github.com/WICG/web-app-launch/issues/92\n\nSee other related spec at https://wicg.github.io/web-app-launch/#launching-a-web-app-with-handling",
  "devtrial_instructions": null,
  "activation_risks": "None, this makes the feature behave in a more predictable manner.",
  "measurement": "Adoption can be measured via the file handling launch feature counter: https://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/3875",
  "availability_expectation": null,
  "adoption_expectation": null,
  "adoption_plan": null,
  "initial_public_proposal_url": null,
  "explainer_links": [],
  "requires_embedder_support": false,
  "spec_link": "https://wicg.github.io/manifest-incubations/index.html#execute-a-file-handler-launch",
  "api_spec": false,
  "automation_spec": false,
  "interop_compat_risks": "Interoperability risk: Low. This aligns with the consensus that reloads should not be treated as new file launches.\n\nCompatibility risk: Low. Theoretically some PWAs may exist that rely on this behavior to \"recover\" file handles after a crash or a manual refresh, and these applications will now need to use persistent storage (like IndexedDB) to track active file handles across sessions. However, given the low usage, it seems unlikely this is the case: https://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/3875",
  "all_platforms": null,
  "all_platforms_descr": "LaunchQueue / Web App Launch, and File Handling is not yet supported on Android.",
  "non_oss_deps": null,
  "anticipated_spec_changes": null,
  "security_risks": "This change is privacy-neutral or slightly positive, as it ensures that file handles are not unnecessarily re-exposed to the application script purely via a page refresh.",
  "ergonomics_risks": "This significantly improves ergonomics by removing the need for \"deduplication\" or \"reload-detection\" boilerplate in the launch consumer.",
  "wpt": null,
  "wpt_descr": "Unfortunately there are no web platform tests for file handling.",
  "webview_risks": null,
